* Support managing calendars, travel, preparing for presentations, company meetings and other key events;
* Assemble and coordinate key project status information related to development and release;
* Plan travel itineraries and make travel arrangements, including reservations for events and dining as needed;
* Prepare, compile and manage expense reports for travel following established company and travel policy guidelines;
* Assist with general department tasks, including conference room requests, ordering supplies, coordinating general maintenance and upgrades for office equipment, phones, computers, etc.;
* Coordinate both on-site and off-site workshops, events and demos, including internal and external partners, vendors, and collaborators;
* Partner and work extensively with internal departments and external vendors to provide and/or receive necessary information, materials, approvals, updates, etc.; and
* Greet guests and assist with special projects relating to guests/visitors.

* General administrative experience supporting executives in a corporate environment;
* Strong written and verbal communication;
* Ability to successfully interact with a wide range of Imagineers, senior executives, vendors;
* Willingness to experiment with new forms of asynchronous communication as our hybrid workstyle continues to evolve;
* High interest in technology and software product development; and
* A culture add.

* Experience at The Walt Disney Company;
* Experience working with Imagineering a plus;
* Experience working in a large public corporation; and
* Experience with video Teleconferencing (VTC) equipment, Slack, Zoom.

* Manage all phases of the market research process including identifying research needs, project design, research methodology design, analysis, and presentation of results;
* Observe, track, and analyze trends in consumer behavior, lifestyle and value changes and work with partners to explore future business opportunities and identify challenges; 
* Extract objective, clear and actionable insights based on the findings of different data and studies so that senior management can make decisions based on facts; 
* Present key findings and recommendations to senior management and other relevant personnel;
* Maintain good working relationships with partners in different business units to help them solve business problems with consumer insights and to ensure that business strategies are developed from a consumer perspective; 
* Manage external primary research and data vendors and build strategic partnerships with them.

* Bachelor’s degree or above;
* 3 to 5+ years of hands-on experience in the field of consumer insights;
* Proficiency in a variety of qualitative and quantitative research methods, with experience in future research and product innovation workshops preferred;
* Good critical thinker able to identify core issues and design research solutions in a complex business environment; 
* Ability to apply innovative research methods to solve problems；
* Ability to extract consumer insights from data and interviews as a means of generating business insights and recommendations, and to present research findings clearly;
* Skilled at team communication and collaboration and able to manage conflicts of interest between parties;
* Outstanding problem-solving skills;
* Possessing good presentation skills;
* Fluency in spoken and written English and Mandarin.

Responsibilities include, but not limited to:

* Think ahead about little things that can turn into big problems and be proactive in finding a solution; 
* Prioritize workload according to Project deadlines and handle interruptions through-out the day with an approachable attitude and assist Project Team when an emergency arises;
* Use teamwork to do the job better, faster, smarter;
* Plan events like birthdays, service anniversary recognition parties, lunch-and-learns and team-building activities;
* Assist with on-boarding new employees – you’ll be the “friendly face” that newbies count on to answer all their questions;
* Schedule meetings, along with reserving a conference room, for the Project Team. In most cases (given the bi-coastal nature of the project), set-up meeting with Zoom video calls;
* Develop working knowledge of conference room systems and assist Project Team when needed;
* Order food for breakfast/lunch meetings and assist with set-up/clean-up;
* Assist in planning Team events, including in-office functions, virtual gatherings (via Zoom), and remote events (at/near Disneyland Resort, at/near Glendale offices, etc);
* Via Concur and American Express, book travel for Project Team as well as RSR requests for contractors and vendors as needed. Prior to booking any travel, ensure Travel Authorization has been signed and approved by the Project Team Leadership and Finance. Also secure required job number for expensing;
* Via Concur, complete expense reports on behalf of Team members;
* Enter backstage gate clearances into EZ Lobby as requested by Project Team;
* If requested, take meeting notes for any Project Team meeting;
* Work with Direct Leader to incorporate additions, changes, or deletions within the Project Team into seating arrangements and tap access into the building;
* Obtain Green Badges for Project Contractors, Independent Contractors, and Vendors;
* Generate Purchase Orders and check requests, as needed, in SAP;
* Make an inventory of the office supplies, then devise a more efficient way to keep things in stock for your specific Project Team;
* Adhere to Project Intellectual Protection Guidelines by watermarking confidential documents, posting onto Project Team BOX sites, as needed, and securing/shredding documents left at printers, plotters, or conference rooms;
* Enter your time into required system (SAP or IQN) on a weekly basis by following the company’s guideline for Accurate Time Recording; and
* Complete all required Computer Based Training in D-Learn in a timely manner.

* Minimum two years in a Secretary role;
* Strong organizational and follow-through skills, orderly and detail-oriented with ability to handle multiple work streams simultaneously, prioritize work and accurately and efficiently archive documents and work products Ability to appropriately respond to and resolve issues with little direction;
* Excellent written, verbal and interpersonal communication skills to assure professional interaction with senior executives, internal partners, and external contacts;
* Strong command of English grammar skills with an ability to prepare correspondence from notes, meetings and author documents and reports;
* Ability to work effectively in a team environment;
* Ability to manage time wisely and prioritize effectively;
* Ability to anticipate needs, take initiative, proactively solve problems and use sound judgment;
* Demonstrated ability to handle confidential and sensitive information;
* Enthusiastic attitude and strong work ethic; and
* Strong computer/technology skills, including but not limited to Microsoft Outlook, Concur, SAP (T&E, Life Events, Time Processor, Employee ESS, Casual Buyer), Internet Explorer and internet-based research, and video teleconferencing systems and services.

Product and Design interns will have opportunities to have internship in Digital Product Management, Enterprise Technology, Innovation & Integration or Project Management Office. You will not only learn Disney's legendary culture, collaborate with amazing Cast Members, experience professional on-job training and career development guidance. 

• You will use data to understand guest behaviors and performance of features;
• You will support execution of commercial tasks or initiative in relation to digital platforms;
• You will collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams (Engineering, Design, Data, etc.) in the development of project timeline;
• You will participate in innovation programs from grounds-up;
• You will work with designers, product owners, and engineers to build high-quality and user-friendly products following Disney brand guidelines;
• You will participate in a cross-functional communication and design presentation to different lines-of-business;
• You will look for innovation in program execution from promotional tactic to the graphic and creative approach;
• You will reflects the guest's voice, determine guest pain points and needs;
• You will define the vision of new products and develop the product roadmap, solutions, requirements;
• You will collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams (Engineering, Design, Data, etc.) to bring ideas to life;
• You will participate in translating functions and information into emotionally compelling experiences that fulfill our guests’ needs and drive business goals.

• Students of Bachelor's degree in Design, Marketing or equivalent practical experience, who are going to graduate between May and September, 2023; student of Master's degree would be a plus; 
• Commit to work for at least 3days per week for a minimum of 6 consecutive months;
• With mobile product design or E-commerce or related internship experience preferred;
• Passionate about the technologies, mobile, internet, and e-commerce;
• Software tool: Skills in Excel, Word, PowerPoint; 
• For design role, proficiency in Sketch, Figma (or other prototyping tools), Adobe C-Suite (After Effect, Photoshop, Illustrator), specifically with mobile app design and multimedia presentation; 
• For design role, Knowledge of typography, color theory, layout design, and design process;
• For design role, a portfolio of your work exhibiting design knowledge and skills;
• Innate passion for Disney and learning product design technologies and trends;
• Understand China markets as well as mobile & internet trends;
• Ability to embrace and adapt to changes and learn quickly in a fast-paced environment;
• Ability to collaborate as part of a team or ideate independently;
• Ability to think creatively, logically and structurally;
• Good team work and learning attitude；
• Good communication and presentation skills in both Mandarin and English.

Engineering interns will have opportunities to have internship in Digital Engineering, Enterprise Technology, Innovation & Integration, Information Security or Testing team. You will not only learn Disney's legendary culture, collaborate with amazing Cast Members, experience professional on-job training and career development guidance. 

• You will assist in system setup and configuration with solid knowledge in computer systems;
• You will analyze business requirements with different teams with great communication and presentation skills;
• You will assist in the solution design process by analyzing feasibility and creating solution diagrams;
• You will analyze, create and manage technical requirements with Agile tools like JIRA;
• You will assist in web development or automation test development underpinned by technologies like Java, JavaScript, Kotlin or Swift;
• You will assist basic triage of technical issues and writing of technical documents like Wi-Ki pages, project reports and system manuals etc.
• You will cooperate with groups across the world, create the leading product in the industry.

• Students of Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or equivalent practical experience, who are going to graduate between May and September, 2023; student of Master's degree would be a plus; 
• Commit to work for at least 3 days per week for a minimum of 6 consecutive months;
• Good understanding about UX and digital design.
• Mobile product design or E-commerce or related internship experience is preferred;
• Passionate about the technologies, mobile, internet, and e-commerce;
• Solid on JavaScript and Vue; 
• Skills in Excel, Word, PowerPoint
• Understand China markets as well as mobile & internet trends;
• Ability to embrace and adapt to changes and learn quickly in a fast-paced environment;
• Ability to collaborate as part of a team or ideate independently;
• Ability to think creatively, logically and structurally;
• Good team work and learning attitude；
• Good communication and presentation skills in both Mandarin and English.

You would join a unit whose mission is to keep everything working perfectly – it’s all about minimizing downtime and maximizing Guest experience. Your skills will help keep the kids smiling and the parents feeling relaxed and secure.
Every day as an Electronic Technician is different. On any given day or night, you might:
* Be called to repair circuits/assemblies at Pirates of the Caribbean; 
* Troubleshoot high-efficiency laser lighting systems for one of the Main Street parades;
* Re-set breakers on the Haunted Mansion;
* Perform preventive maintenance on the rides in Toy Story Land; 
* Repair and maintain electrical/electronic systems/assemblies on It’s A Small World;
* Replace/install lamps and switches to keep the parks light and bright;
* Insure the Monorail hums along with PLC preventive maintenance;
* Work on animations like the Yeti on the Matterhorn, on R2D2, and on the Little Mermaid;
* Use your experience and know-how to spot problems before they happen;
* Experience the Parks at night, when the Guests have left and it’s just you and the rides; and 
* Enjoy Disney with your exclusive Cast Member perks, including steep discounts on things people like you

We proudly and enthusiastically welcome Electronic Technicians with experience in the US Military. 
To be successful in this role, you will need:
Technical competence, the ability to read and understand detailed instructions, blueprints, flowcharts, schematics and engineering documents, and pass all compliance necessary for technical and safety training;
Knowledge of control and repair of circuits and motor;
Sharp troubleshooting skills and comfort working alone or as part of a team;
Ability to evaluate the scope of a job, determine needed parts/materials, and order through authorized vendors.
Expertise using common hand tools, meters, gauges and other associated test and measurement equipment, as well as ability to measure current, voltage and amperage;
Mastery of the basic math skills needed to do the job, the ability to differentiate colors, computer literacy, and full understanding of the National Electric Code;
Familiarity with CCTV systems, audio/public address systems, theatrical lighting fixtures, video projectors and wireless networks;
Reliable on-time behavior and the flexibility to work at night as well as on weekends/holidays;
Good communication skills with outside vendors as well as fellow Cast Members, a Guest/customer focus, high energy, respect for diversity, reliability, and a can-do, team-first attitude;
Stamina and the physical ability to undertake the job. You might walk, bicycle, bend, kneel, climb, push vehicles to re-position them for repair, work with arms/hands above shoulder level for an extended period of time, climb (sometimes as high as 200 ft.) and more, all on a regular basis. 
Ability to use 2-way radios, learn CMMS (MAXIMO work order system), and attend/pass compliance and other training sessions to ensure correct maintenance documentation. 

Electronic Technicians may work outdoors in all weather conditions, in an industrial workshop, in kitchens with wet/slippery surfaces, and may have occasional exposure to high temperatures, noise levels and fumes. In addition to the physical tasks listed above, Electronic Technicians may need to push/pull and/or lift up to 10 lbs. constantly, up to 25 lbs. frequently, up to 75 lbs. occasionally, and rarely up to/over 100 lbs.

